# ip2region xdb datasets are not committed — they're either fetched
# via `make data` (calls scripts/fetch-ip2region.sh) or shipped
# alongside the binary in release tarballs. Embedding them in the Go
# binary inflates platypus-server by ~11 MB (v4) and ~36 MB (v6) for
# data most operators don't need at runtime.
*.xdb
